MASTERS TOURNAMENT
April 6, 2012
Lee Westwood
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 Q.   How difficult was the course playing today, different from yesterday?  
LEE WESTWOOD:   Well, it's a lot more breeze, obviously, which makes it play tougher.   The greens are obviously drying out and getting a bit faster.   And then obviously you know the wind can play havoc with some of the second shots.  
   
 Q.   Is the mud still being a problem on the ‑‑  
LEE WESTWOOD:   I only had it on the ball on one hole and that's 17.   So it's ‑‑ there is no excuse right now, I don't think.  
   
 Q.   Overall are you pleased with the day?  
LEE WESTWOOD:   Yeah, I'm going to finish and I'm not going to be too far off the lead.   That's a position you want to be (inaudible).   
   
  
  
  
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT